Ing '''kuse''' (''Allium tuberosum''), a '''garlic chives''' o '''green nira grass''' king Ingles<ref name=telegraph-norrington-davies-2006>{{cite news|last=Norrington-Davies|first=Tom|title=Spring it on them|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/foodanddrink/recipes/3325176/Spring-it-on-them.html|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=17 May 2012|date=8 April 2006}}</ref>) ampong '''kuntsay''' king Tagalug ampong Cebuanu, metung yang guleng kamaganak ning [[sibuyas]]. Aliwa ya pamandagul ing tanaman, a maki makayaliwang bulung a katabas sinturun, <ref name="TBC">{{cite book | last =McGee | first =Rose Marie Nichols  | authorlink = | coauthors = Stuckey, Maggie | title =The Bountiful Container | publisher = Workman Publishing | year = 2002}}</ref> a e ra kalupa deng bulung ning [[sibuyas]] o [[bawang]]. at maki matulid yang payat a tangkeng maputi, a matas a e mu nanu kesa kareng bulung. Mas malapit ya lasa king bawang.<ref name="TBC"/>  Tutubu ya kareng kumpul a bagya-bagyang lalapad, oneng gad ya muring tutubu ibat kareng butul.

